NOTE: these are UK specific laws

computer misuse act (CMA)
  section 1 makes it an offense to gain unauthorized access to computer material (systems or data)
  section 2 makes it an offense to gain unauthorized access with intent to commit or facilitate further offenses
  section 3 makes it an offense to perform unauthorized acts against computer systems (even if accidental)
  section 3A criminalizes the making, supplying, or obtaining of any programs/data which could hold malware or hacking instructions
  sections 3ZA enforces harsher sentencing for unauthorized acts which cause significant risk or damage to human welfare/national security
  
human rights act
  it is essential that activites of a security assessment do not infrige upon an individual's privacy rights

data protection act & GDPR
  lawfulness: processing of personal data but have a valid legal basis and be compliant w/ requirements
  fairness: any data processing must be fair towards the individual, not misleading or deceptive
  transparency: controllers must provide individuals with information regarding the processing of their data in a readable format
  purpose limitation: data must be collected for a specific and legit purpose 
  data minimization: only collect and process data that is relevant and limited to what is needed for intended purposes
  accuracy: data must be accurate and kept up-to-date
  storage limitation: controllers must not hold on to personal data for longer than is necessary
  accountability: controllers are responsible for compliance with all above principles

sector legislation:
  financial services and markets act: regulates financial services sector 
  payment services regulations: governs payments services and set security requirements
  health & social care act: governs the delivery health and social care services and provisions the protection and confidentiality of patient data
  digital operational resilience act (DORA): aims to strengthen IT security of financial entities

  CBEST: framework that aligns various regulatory requirements, specifically for financial institutions
  TIBER-EU: framework for conducting threat intelligence led ethical red teaming 
